<dl id="n42031a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42031a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42031a"> 31(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cross on back / pillar in front / chasuble</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Bishop sends by a nun of the Ursuline Convent of Three Rivers a present to Mr. Chiniquy, consisting of a chasuble, or the embroidered garment with a cross on the back, and a pillar in front, worn by priests; <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) x</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
